riscv-mini-os
=============

This project is a RISC-V kernel built on top of the educational starter code
distributed for ECE 391 (Computer Systems Engineering) at the University of
Illinois at Urbana-Champaign.

Origin
------
- Starter scaffolding (build system layout, device drivers stubs, machine
  papering, header conventions, test bench harness) was authored by the
  ECE 391 Course Staff at UIUC and is distributed under the University of
  Illinois/NCSA Open Source License (see LICENSE).
- All starter source files retain their original copyright notice and
  SPDX-License-Identifier header. Removing or modifying these notices is
  not permitted under the NCSA license terms.

Modifications and additions
---------------------------
- Substantive kernel implementation (memory subsystem, virtual memory,
  process model, syscall layer, KTFS read/write, scheduler, traps, page
  fault handling, ELF loader integration, fork/exec semantics, the test
  bench cases), the user-mode shell, the pure-Python `mkfs_ktfs` toolchain,
  documentation, and CI configuration were authored by Yoonkyu Lee
  (yoonguri21@gmail.com) in 2024-2026 and are also distributed under the
  University of Illinois/NCSA Open Source License.

